  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-02 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; twelve factors meet or exceed their required levels. One factor — Model Form — carries a required level of 3 but an achieved level of 2. The decision record accepts the package on the basis of compensating evidence across the remaining factors, expert judgment from three independent hemolysis modelling specialists, and Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification results that bound the hemolysis index below the clinical threshold with 95% confidence. The structural shortfall in Model Form is not formally closed by these arguments, constituting a rebutting defeater (W-AR-02) against the Accepted outcome.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-absolute-threshold",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cou2-vad-hemolysis-credibility",
